<h2>Butt Joint Glazed Windows</h2>
Butt joint glazed windows are a true architectural feature available from Solar Innovations<sup>Â®</sup>.Â This unique glazing option creates a frameless corner window consisting of two pieces of glass that are joined together at a 90 degree angle, without any metal framing attached to the corner.Â  The end result is a modern architectural window with a contemporary appeal.Â  Because there is no corner framing, the window provides unobstructed views.

In order to achieve such a unique result, the glass employed in the window must be engineered as a structural element, resulting in a strict range of glass size and thickness dictated by code requirements. Structural glazing also features horizontal (top and bottom) supports, similar to that of a clear wall, to ensure the appropriate structural loads can be achieved. These windows often perform equal to or better than a conventional framing system when properly installed and engineered.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/4"][vc_column_text]
